<para style="p">For the chief musician; A psalm of David, a song.</para>

<para style="b" />

<para style="q1">

<verse number="1" style="v" />Let God arise; let his enemies be scattered;</para>

<para style="q1">let those also who hate him flee before him.</para>

<para style="q1">

<verse number="2" style="v" />As smoke is driven away, so drive them away;</para>

<para style="q1">as wax melts before the fire,</para>

<para style="q1">so let the wicked perish in the presence of God.</para>

<para style="q1">

<verse number="3" style="v" />But let the righteous be glad; let them exult before God;</para>

<para style="q1">may they rejoice and be happy.</para>
